        "title": "How to transform elements to widgets?",
        "body": "<p>I'm working on a GWT website generated with elements:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>DivElement footerElement = Document.get().createDivElement();\nfooterElement.setAttribute(\"id\", \"mainFooter\");\n\nHeadingElement headingElement = Document.get().createHElement(2);\nheadingElement.setInnerText(\"This is a footer block\");\n\nRootPanel.get().add(footerElement );\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>I want to test some layout panels disposals, but I read that I can only add widgets to layout panels.<\/p>\n\n<p>Are they some way to transform my elements into widgets without write again all my IHM?<\/p>\n",
